# Production deployment safety

Production: **https://connectintel.net** (Vercel `connect-intel`).

## Before pushing to main

1. Run `npm run prod:ship` (build + missing-file checks).
2. Follow `docs/RELEASE_CHECKLIST.md` for manual smoke items when the change is user-facing.

## After push (Vercel Production Ready)

1. Run `npm run prod:log` — updates `docs/PRODUCTION_LOG.md` and auto-triggers `prod:ops` (Meilisearch sync) on new LIVE commit.
2. Confirm new commit shows **← LIVE**.
3. If search/index ops did not run, manually: `npm run prod:ops` (all orgs) or `npm run prod:ops -- --name=Xindus`.
4. Optional known-good marker: `npm run prod:tag -- <commit>` then `git push origin --tags`.

## If production breaks

1. `npm run prod:rollback -- <commit>` (from PRODUCTION_LOG.md).
2. Fix forward on main; do not force-push unless the user explicitly requests it.

## CI

GitHub Actions runs the same build on every push/PR to `main`. Do not merge broken builds.

## Scope

Do not commit Android/Capacitor unless the user explicitly includes them in deploy scope.
